The paper focuses on the application of deep learning algorithms in wireless communications, specifically in the analog channel state information (CSI) feedback process. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category, which deals with the study of communication systems and their limits. Additionally, the paper discusses the effect of adversarial attacks on DL-based communication systems, which could fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also analyzes the performance of normalized mean square error, which is a common metric in the Networked Systems (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper raises concerns regarding the security of DL-based algorithms, which could fall under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
